folder: Bank Street & Greenwich Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
101-117 Bank Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Greenwich Street, seen across the clearing on the S.W. corner, where 764-770 Greenwich Street ant 102-106 Bank Street have been demolished.  No. 113-115, the low white building is or is shortly to be tenanted by the Asia Noodle Company; it was formerly occupied by the Magnolia Metal Company.

July 17, 1932

P.L. Sperr

folder: Greenwich Street & Bank Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
767-761 Greenwich Street, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of Bank Street, as seen through clearance on the S.W. corner. No. 767 is a 1-story frame structure. Elevated shown, is the Ninth Ave. Line.

July 17, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Bank Street & Greenwich Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Bank Street, at, adjoining and west of the N. W. corner of Greenwich Street. View 2 is limited to the building at the corner. Note the 9th Avenue "El" line on Greenwich Street. This feature is under demolition at this date.

May 12, 1940
No's. 1-2

P. L. Sperr
